Defendant Shannon  Owensby in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee files an amended information with the court; amending counts 1, 2 & 3 to Misd. failure to support and adding counts 4 & 5 of the same.
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to all 5 counts.  Atty Gumz agrees and states the defendant did get a copy of the amended information and waives the reading.  Atty Gumz enters a No Contest plea.  
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Counts 1, 2, 3, 4 & 5.

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.
Atty Gumz makes sentencing arguments.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  Counts 1 - 5:  Withhold Sentence; 36 months Probation with conditions:
90 days in the Marquette County Jail w/huber on Ct. 1; impose and stay
Court Costs = $243.00 on each count
Comply with any counseling or treatment recommended by the Agent
Comply with all requirements of Child Support Agency
No increase of the arrears balance as of January 9th
